```hcl
# Example Terraform configuration for associating a VPC with a Route 53 Hosted Zone

# Data source to fetch an existing public hosted zone
data "aws_route53_zone" "example" {
  name         = "example.com"  # Replace with your domain name
  private_zone = false
}

# Data source to fetch an existing VPC
data "aws_vpc" "example" {
  filter {
    name   = "tag:Name"
    values = ["example-vpc"]  # Replace with your VPC name or ID
  }
}

# Associate VPC with the public hosted zone (for public DNS resolution in VPC)
resource "aws_route53_zone_association" "example" {
  zone_id = data.aws_route53_zone.example.zone_id
  vpc_id  = data.aws_vpc.example.id

  # Optional: Specify additional VPC regions for multi-region associations
  # vpc_region = "us-west-2"
}

# Output the hosted zone ID and association details
output "hosted_zone_id" {
  description = "ID of the Route 53 hosted zone"
  value       = data.aws_route53_zone.example.zone_id
}

output "zone_association_id" {
  description = "ID of the hosted zone association"
  value       = aws_route53_zone_association.example.id
}
```

**Prerequisites:**
- Replace `"example.com"` with your actual domain name.
- Ensure the VPC exists and update the filter to match your VPC.
- This example shows a **public hosted zone** association with a VPC (common for private resolution of public domains within VPC).
- For **private hosted zones**, set `private_zone = true` in the data source and ensure proper VPC permissions.

