**Note:** This configuration creates a primary MySQL RDS instance in us-west-1 with read replicas in the three other regions. Weighted Route 53 routing distributes traffic approximately equally (33/33/34 weights) across all four endpoints (primary + 3 replicas). The hosted zone is named "main" and uses example.com domain. All DB instances are publicly accessible for Route 53 CNAME routing. Adjust security groups and VPC configurations for production use.

