## Authentication Usage

To authenticate using IAM with this ElastiCache cluster:

```bash
# Using redis-cli with IAM auth
aws elasticache auth --username elasticache-iam-user \n  --cluster-endpoint ${aws_elasticache_replication_group.redis_iam.primary_endpoint_address}:6379 \n  --region us-west-2

# Or using Redis CLI with AUTH
redis-cli -h ${aws_elasticache_replication_group.redis_iam.primary_endpoint_address} -p 6379
> AUTH $username:$access_key_id
```

**Key Points:**
- IAM database authentication is enabled via `transit_encryption_enabled = true`
- The IAM policy grants `elasticache-db:auth` permission
- Clients authenticate using `username:access_key_id` format
- Both static password and IAM auth can work simultaneously

