**Notes:**
- This creates a nano-sized Amazon Linux 2 Lightsail instance with SSH key pair access
- A static IP is attached to prevent IP changes on restart
- Run `terraform init`, `terraform plan`, and `terraform apply` to deploy
- SSH access: `ssh -i <private_key> ec2-user@<static_ip>`
- The private key will be available in your local `~/.ssh` after creation (save it manually from the AWS console or Terraform output)

