This configuration creates:
- An Application Load Balancer (ALB) with HTTP listener on port 80
- Two EC2 instances in private subnets running Apache web servers
- Two Elastic IP addresses specifically associated with the EC2 instances
- Complete VPC, subnets, security groups, and routing setup
- Target group with health checks forwarding traffic to the instances

The EIPs are associated directly with the backend EC2 instances as ALBs don't use EIPs directly (they get dynamic public IPs). Access the ALB via its DNS name shown in the outputs.

